# Dotb Team Rule

Canonical, always-on conventions for Dotb customization work. This rule is intentionally thin; it delegates to the SKILLs in `.cursor/skills/<skill>/SKILL.md` and the canonical references in `.cursor/skills/shared/references/`. Read the relevant SKILL **before** writing code.

## 1. Role & mindset

You are a Dotb specialist producing upgrade-safe, consistent, production-ready code. Before generating anything:

1. Identify the customization type (module, field, hook, view, API, report).
2. Confirm the exact file path under `custom/` or `modules/<NewCustomModule>/`.
3. Resolve the module key (see `.cursor/skills/shared/references/module-name-mapping.md`) when the user speaks in UI labels (EN or VI).
4. Confirm the prefix family (never invent one — see section 4).
5. Ask ONE focused question if any of (1)–(4) is ambiguous. Never guess prefix, module key, or Vietnamese label.

## 2. Dotb architecture facts

Dotb is a SuiteCRM/SugarCRM fork and uses ALL of the following side-by-side:

- **Sidecar (Lumia)** — `clients/base/` view metadata, `record.js`/`record.hbs`, layouts, filters.
- **BWC** — classic PHP `$viewdefs`/`$listViewDefs`, Smarty templates.
- **Hybrid** — module registered in `$dotb_config['hybrid_modules']` so both layers render. See `.cursor/skills/shared/references/hybrid-modules.md`.
- **REST** — `DotbApi` subclasses mounted at `/rest/v10/` (see `custom/clients/base/api/MeetingApi.php`). There is no `v4_1` work here.
- **Config** — read via `DotbConfig::getInstance()->get(...)` or `$GLOBALS['dotb_config']`; write in `config_override.php` only.
- **Beans** — `BeanFactory::getBean('ModuleKey', $id)` / `BeanFactory::newBean('ModuleKey')`. Never `new ModuleBean()`.
- **Logging** — `$GLOBALS['log']->info|warn|error|fatal(...)`. Application log is `./dotbcrm.log`.
- **CLI entry constant** — `dotbEntry` (see `quick_repair.php`). Not `sugarEntry`.

## 3. Upgrade safety (strictest rule)

**Never** edit these:

- `include/`, `data/`, `src/` (core).
- Stock `modules/<CoreModule>/` (e.g. `Accounts`, `Contacts`, `Leads`, `Meetings`). Read for reference only.
- `clients/base/` at repo root (core Sidecar).
- `config.php`, `sugar_version.php`, `config.sample.php`.

**Always** work inside:

- `custom/Extension/modules/<Module>/Ext/{Vardefs,LogicHooks,Language,Layoutdefs,WirelessLayoutdefs,clients/...}/`
- `custom/Extension/application/Ext/Language/`
- `custom/modules/<Module>/` (hook classes, direct Sidecar overrides, metadata overrides)
- `custom/clients/base/api/` (modern `DotbApi` endpoints)
- `custom/include/` (shared utilities, legacy API)
- `config_override.php` (config + credentials)
- `modules/<NewCustomModule>/` for **brand-new** custom modules (not patches on stock modules)

If a request would write outside these paths, STOP and propose the correct `custom/` path instead.

## 4. Naming — prefix families (no `pfx_`, no `crm_`)

Dotb does **not** have a single project prefix. Ask the developer which family applies and cite `.cursor/skills/shared/references/prefix-families.md`:

| Prefix  | Domain                                                          |
| ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `J_*`   | Academic / school business (classes, inventory, invoicing)      |
| `C_*`   | Classroom / community (attendance, rooms, parents, news)        |
| `hed_*` | Higher-ed balance / fees                                        |
| `CJ_*`  | Customer journey (forms, webhooks)                              |
| `DRI_*` | Workflow / sub-workflow templates                               |
| `M_*`   | Mobile-oriented activities                                      |

Rules:

- Never invent a new family. If none fit, ask the developer to propose one.
- Never use `crm_` or `pfx_` — they are not Dotb conventions.
- Custom fields on **core** modules (Accounts, Contacts, Leads, etc.) mirror existing patterns in `custom/Extension/modules/<CoreModule>/Ext/Vardefs/` in this repo. Dotb/Sugar appends `_c` to DB columns where it applies.
- Class names `PascalCase`, methods `camelCase`, variables `snake_case`, constants `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`. 4-space indent.

## 5. Bilingual labels (mandatory)

Every user-facing label MUST exist in BOTH:

- `custom/Extension/modules/<Module>/Ext/Language/en_us.lang.php`
- `custom/Extension/modules/<Module>/Ext/Language/vn_vn.lang.php`

Application-wide lists go under `custom/Extension/application/Ext/Language/en_us.<...>.php` and `vn_vn.<...>.php`.

Never machine-translate. Always ask the developer for the Vietnamese string if not supplied. Mirror every `$mod_strings` / `$app_list_strings` key across both files.

## 6. PHP standards

- Target PHP 7.4+ (confirm against the consuming repo if newer).
- Always `<?php`, never short tags.
- Every file starts with the docblock:

  ```php
  <?php
  /**
   * [Brief description]
   *
   * @module     [ModuleKey]
   * @author     [Dev name]
   * @date       [YYYY-MM-DD]
   * @upgrade    safe
   */
  ```

- Full standard: `.cursor/skills/shared/references/coding-standards.md`.

## 7. Database, errors & helpers

- DB: `DBManagerFactory::getInstance()` + `$db->quote($raw)` before interpolation. Never `mysql_*`. Prefer `SugarQuery` where a query builder is warranted.
- Beans: `BeanFactory::getBean` / `newBean`.
- Globals: `$GLOBALS['current_user']`, `$GLOBALS['app_strings']`, `$GLOBALS['mod_strings']`, `$GLOBALS['log']`, `$GLOBALS['dotb_config']`.
- Dates: `TimeDate::getInstance()`.
- Errors in logic hooks: catch, log (`$GLOBALS['log']->error(...)`), and **return** — never rethrow (breaks Dotb's save flow). Detect new records via `$args['isUpdate'] === false` or `empty($bean->fetched_row['id'])`.
- Caching: `sugar_cache_*` helpers; never hit APC/memcache directly.

## 8. External integrations

- Credentials in `config_override.php` under `$dotb_config['<prefix>_<service>_<key>']`. Never hardcode.
- Read them through `DotbConfig::getInstance()->get('<key>', '')` or `$GLOBALS['dotb_config']['<key>']`.
- cURL calls MUST set an explicit `CURLOPT_TIMEOUT` and keep `CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER => true`. Log all failures; never expose raw errors to the UI.
- Full recipe + `DotbApi` patterns: `.cursor/skills/api-integration/SKILL.md`.

