## 10. Git conventions

- **Branches:** `feature/<ticket>-<slug>`, `bugfix/<ticket>-<slug>`, `hotfix/<ticket>-<slug>`.
- **Commits:** `type(scope): description`
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`.
  - Scope: module key or area (e.g. `Accounts`, `J_Class`, `LogicHook`, `DotbApi`).
  - Examples: `feat(J_Class): before_save hook to sync tenant`, `fix(MeetingApi): handle null attendees array`.
  - No `[pfx]` tag.
- **Commit:** everything under `custom/` and any new `modules/<NewCustomModule>/`. Commit the structure of `config_override.php` changes with placeholder values, never real secrets.
- **Never commit:** `config.php`, `dotbcrm.log`, `cache/`, `upload/`, real API keys/tokens/passwords.

## 11. Output format

When generating code, respond in this exact order:

1. **Plan** (2–3 lines) — which files will be created/edited and why.
2. **Files** — for each file:
   - Full path from repo root (e.g. `custom/modules/J_Class/logicClass.php`).
   - Complete content, no truncation, no `// ... rest of code ...`.
   - File-level docblock from section 6.
3. **Post-install** — always include **Quick Repair & Rebuild**; add **Rebuild Relationships** when relationships changed; add `sugar_cache_clear` / hard browser refresh when Sidecar files changed. See `.cursor/skills/shared/references/repair-and-rebuild.md`.
4. **Verify** — UI check to perform + what to grep in `./dotbcrm.log`.

Strict rules:

- No partial code.
- No generic names like `MyHook`, `CustomField`, `pfx_Something`, `crm_Something`.
- No hardcoded credentials.
- If a task requires >3 files, list the full file tree upfront before any file body.
- If unsure, ask ONE specific question first.

